snippet.textDisplay: I once had a bad experience with a popcorn machine, it was the middle of summer and I didn't drink enough water and at the local university owned surplus warehouse the employees had fixed up a donated popcorn machine. I was unsure if I should have any since it was incredibly hot, but I was also somewhat hungry. My mom and I were done browsing the absurd voluminous collections of out of date technology, bikes, tables, and chairs of all kinds, but she noticed me continuously looking back at the popcorn machine and asked if I wanted some. It was the worst mistake I made that year, I tried some and immediately felt like stopping but when my mom and I got in her car I started feeling increasingly hungrier. The only food we had that I could eat during the drive was the popcorn, which the heat of the car, the increase of thirst, and backseat did not mix well with. I felt incredibly nauseous because of it.
